# Markdown File Metadata Standard

All Markdown files (`.md`) in this workspace should begin with a YAML frontmatter block enclosed in `---`. This block contains standard metadata fields.

**Standard Fields:**

*   `title`: (String) The main title of the page.
*   `description`: (String) A brief summary of the page content under 140 characters.
*   `published`: (Boolean) `true` or `false` indicating if the page is live.
*   `date`: (String) The last updated date in ISO 8601 format (e.g., `YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ss.sssZ`).
*   `tags`: (String) A comma-separated list of relevant keywords (kebab-case).
*   `editor`: (String) Should typically be `markdown`.
*   `dateCreated`: (String) The original creation date in ISO 8601 format.
*   `fontawesomeIcon`: (String, Optional) A Font Awesome icon class (e.g., `fa-layer-group`) if applicable.

Adherence to this structure ensures consistency across the wiki.

